<div id="header_ctt">
TextBot.
</div>

<div id="content">
TextBot is a simple and automatic text file processing application. It can be used to apply small changes to a file or apply string changes using
the strong language C# and a set of tools that can be used while processing file.
<p>
<h1>Usage</h1>
The C# code on the left side will compile before each execution.
Remember to create namespace Generated, class GeneratedClass and method Process because this is the entry point of the program.
</p>
<p>
<h1>Predefined functions</h1>
Predefined functions on the application:
<h2>void Clear()</h2>
Clear all the output panel.
<h2>void Write(string s)</h2>
Write an string to the output (no CRLF will be appended).
<h2>void Write(params object[] os)</h2>
Write a set of strings just one behind the other.
<h2>void WriteLine(string s)</h2>
Write an string on the output and jump to next line.
<h2>void WriteLine(params object[] os)</h2>
Write a set of string just one behind other and jump to a new line.
<h2>void WriteNewLine()</h2>
new line jump (CRLF)
<h2>void SetInput(string s)</h2>
Set the string as new input text.
<h2>void ClearInput()</h2>
Clear the input panel.
<h2>void WriteInput(string s)</h2>
Same as Write() but for the input panel
<h2>string WGet(string url)</h2>
Returns an string with all the contents at specified URL. Useful with SetInput to process online content.
<h2>string NormalizeLines(string data)</h2>
detects new line codes (CRLF,CR,LF) and replace all to DOS/Windows ones (CRLF).
<h2>string GetString()</h2>
Read all the input into a single string.
<h2>string[] GetLines()</h2>
Get all input lines as an array of strings.
</p>
